  "prompt": "What if Obama dies before Trump is inaugurated? Would Joe Biden assume presidency or Trump take oath earlier than planned?",
  "response": "If President Barack Obama were to die before Donald Trump was inaugurated, the situation would still adhere to the established constitutional procedures. In this scenario, Joe Biden, as the sitting Vice President, would not assume the presidency, since he would be leaving office at the same time as Obama. \n\nInstead, the transition would proceed as planned. Donald Trump would take the oath of office on January 20, 2017, as scheduled, assuming the presidency at that time. The death of a sitting president does not change the inauguration date for the president-elect. \n\nThe 20th Amendment to the U.S. Constitution outlines the presidential transition and specifies that the terms of the president and vice president end at noon on January 20th, and the newly elected president is then inaugurated at that time. Therefore, if Obama were to pass away before that date, Trump would still be inaugurated as planned, and all procedures surrounding that event would continue as per the constitutional guidelines.",
